LADY MARY WORTLEY MONTAGU
----------------------------------------------------------------------

    The historian F.C Hodgson described her as "one of our undoubted
    Twickenham celebrities". Others saw her as an adventurer, an
    orientalist, a medical pioneer, a correspondent with the good and
    great and a heart breaker too.

    Lady Mary Pierrepont, the eldest child of Evelyn Pierrepont, 1st
    Duke of Kingston-upon-Hull was born in May 1689. Following his
    wife's death in 1692 the Duke passed the care of Mary and her three
    younger siblings to their grandmother.

